oyees%20said%20they%20were%20drawn%20to%20the%20company's%20mission%20and%20the%20chance%20to%20work%20on%20an%20Altman%20project%2C%20some%20questioned%20whether%20it%20had%20a%20clear%20long-term%20strategy.%20Experts%20also%20had%20concerns%20over%20the%20company's%20overall%20viability%20in%20a%20crowded%20marketplace%20for%20both%20payment%20products%20and%20identification%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3EInside%20Business%20is%20today's%20must-read%20story%20on%20what%20the%20forces%20shaping%20business%2C%20tech%2C%20and%20innovation%20mean%20for%20you.%20Each%20piece%20delivers%20insights%20to%20help%20you%20make%20smarter%20career%2C%20money%2C%20and%20life%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20see%20a%20sort%20of%20killer%20use%20case%20that%20they've%20really%20figured%20out%20and%20will%20drive%20major%20traction%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Nick%20Maynard%2C%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20fintech%20market%20research%20at%20global%20tech%20strategist%20firm%20Juniper%20Research%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThere%20needs%20to%20be%20a%20real%20purpose%20to%20exist%2C%20and%20that%20isn't%20super%20clear%20as%20of%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20the%20company%20says%20it%20has%20verified%20around%2017.5%20million%20people%20%E2%80%94%20a%20little%20under%202%25%20of%20its%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225196%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Circular%20wooden%20installation%20with%20orb-shaped%20biometric%20scanners%20at%20World%20(formerly%20Worldcoin)%20location%2C%20Union%20Square%2C%20San%20Francisco%2C%20California%2C%20May%2020%2C%202025.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690e3dc57f37aa653f55a456%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOrbs%20on%20display%20at%20a%20location%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20California.%3Cp%3ESmith%20Collection%2FGado%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20push%20for%20growth%20comes%20as%20it%20faces%20increasingly%20fierce%20regulatory%20headwinds%20globally%2C%20as%20well%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.technologyreview.com%2F2022%2F04%2F06%2F1048981%2Fworldcoin-cryptocurrency-biometrics-web3%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eethical%20concerns%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20its%20collection%20of%20biometric%20data.%20The%20company%20says%20it%20has%20Orbs%20in%20over%2020%20countries%2C%20from%20Mexico%20to%20South%20Korea.%20It%20has%20been%20barred%2C%20halted%2C%20or%20investigated%20in%20many%20countries%2C%20like%20Spain%2C%20India%2C%20and%20Indonesia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20German%20authorities%20investigating%20the%20company%20determined%20that%20its%20data%20protection%20measures%20%26quot%3Bwould%20not%20be%20sufficient%20to%20implement%20an%20appropriate%20level%20of%20security%20with%20regard%20to%20cybercriminals%20or%20state%20attackers.%26quot%3B%20(The%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fworld.org%2Fblog%2Fworld%2Fworld-view-gdpr-anonymization-europe%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20was%20appealing%20that%20decision%2C%20which%20is%20on%20hold%20as%20regulators%20evaluate%20World's%20new%20technology.)%20In%20China%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20State%20Security%20recently%20warned%20that%20collecting%20iris%20data%20for%20crypto%20could%20pose%20a%20national%20security%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%2C%20agencies%20in%20three%20countries%20took%20regulatory%20action.%20The%20National%20Privacy%20Commission%20in%20the%20Philippines%20issued%20a%20cease-and-desist%20order%20to%20stop%20scanning%20eyeballs%20because%20it%20violated%20the%20country's%20data%20privacy%20act%3B%20Colombian%20regulators%20ordered%20it%20to%20immediately%20cease%20operations%20and%20delete%20data%3B%20and%20officials%20in%20Thailand%20raided%20iris%20scanning%20locations%20and%20arrested%20suspects%20%26quot%3Bfor%20operating%20an%20unlicensed%20digital%20asset%20business.%26quot%3B%20The%20company%20said%20it%20is%20appealing%20the%20decision%20in%20Colombia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20a%20Tools%20for%20Humanity%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%2C%20%26quot%3BWorld%20was%20designed%20for%20every%20human%2C%20which%20is%20why%20we%20are%20proud%20to%20have%20launched%20on%20multiple%20continents%2C%20spanning%20fully%20connected%20urban%20centers%20to%20remote%20rural%20areas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20approach%20enables%20the%20project%20to%20reflect%20the%20diversity%20and%20richness%20of%20a%20truly%20global%20human%20network%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20added.%20%26quot%3BAs%20AI%20use%20cases%20continue%20to%20grow%2C%20many%20experts%20agree%20that%20adding%20a%20proof%20of%20human%20layer%20to%20the%20internet%20is%20increasingly%20important%20to%20preserve%20trust%20online.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20without%20access%20to%20the%20world's%20most%20populous%20countries%20%E2%80%94%20and%20as%20international%20regulators%20and%20officials%20ring%20alarm%20bells%20over%20iris-scanning%20practices%20and%20data%20collection%20%E2%80%94%20its%20ambitious%20goals%20may%20be%20increasingly%20difficult%20to%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFundamentally%2C%20if%20it%20continues%20to%20experience%20those%20regulatory%20issues%2C%26quot%3B%20Maynard%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthen%20scale%20will%20be%20an%20impossible%20task.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c41ca11f-37f8-4eb7-a81b-29569ed83aed%5C%22%3E'Sam%20had%20this%20very%20simple%20idea'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELaunched%20in%202019%2C%20Altman%20envisioned%20World%20as%20a%20way%20to%20protect%20against%20a%20growing%20problem%3A%20the%20proliferation%20of%20technology%20that%20mimics%20human%20speech%2C%20behavior%2C%20and%20thought.%20As%20AI%20becomes%20increasingly%20lifelike%2C%20the%20thinking%20goes%2C%20people%20need%20a%20way%20to%20make%20sure%20they're%20interacting%20with%20other%20humans%2C%20not%20bots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20this%20need%20is%20in%20response%20to%20the%20race%20by%20buzzy%20AI%20companies%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-ceos-weigh-in-openai-chief-sam-altman-leadership-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elike%20Altman's%20OpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20create%20models%20that%20can%20convincingly%20replicate%20human%20nature.%20%26quot%3BHe%20is%20creating%20the%20disease%2C%20but%20he%20also%20wants%20to%20create%20the%20cure%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20former%20employee%2C%20who%20was%20involved%20with%20expansion%20in%20Latin%20America%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%2C%20there%20were%20discussions%20of%20integrating%20World%20with%20OpenAI%20to%20verify%20the%20humanness%20of%20those%20using%20its%20services%2C%20according%20to%20two%20former%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20attends%20an%20event%20to%20pitch%20AI%20for%20businesses%20in%20Tokyo%2C%20Japan%20February%203%2C%202025.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690e400a7f37aa653f55a4ba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22534%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESam%20Altman%20envisioned%20World%20as%20a%20way%20to%20protect%20against%20a%20growing%20problem%3A%20the%20proliferation%20of%20technology%20that%20mimics%20human%20speech%2C%20behavior%2C%20and%20thought.%20Part%20of%20this%20need%20is%20in%20response%20to%20the%20race%20by%20buzzy%20AI%20companies%2C%20like%20OpenAI%2C%20to%20create%20models%20that%20can%20convincingly%20replicate%20human%20nature.%3Cp%3EKim%20Kyung-Hoon%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSam%20had%20this%20very%20simple%20idea%2C%26quot%3B%20Alex%20Blania%2C%20Tools%20for%20Humanity's%20CEO%2C%20said%20on%20a%202022%20podcast%3A%20launch%20a%20token%20%26quot%3Bsimply%20for%20being%20a%20human.%26quot%3B%20By%20doing%20that%2C%20Blania%20said%2C%20they%20could%20create%20a%20%26quot%3Breally%2C%20really%20large%20network%2C%26quot%3B%20of%20actual%20people%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20ultimately%2C%20%26quot%3Ba%20network-based%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20may%20tout%20the%20idea%20as%20simple%2C%20but%20the%20corporate%20structure%20is%20more%20complex.%20Tools%20for%20Humanity%20is%20a%20for-profit%20technology%20company%2C%20with%20headquarters%20in%20San%20Francisco%20and%20Munich%3B%20it%20develops%20technology%20for%20World%20like%20the%20Orb.%20The%20World%20project%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%26quot%3Breal%20human%26quot%3B%20network%20%E2%80%94%20is%20controlled%20by%20the%20Cayman%20Island-based%20World%20Foundation.%20The%20foundation%20is%20the%20sole%20director%20of%20the%20British%20Virgin%20Islands-based%20World%20Assets%20Limited%2C%20which%20oversees%20the%20distribution%20of%20Worldcoin%20tokens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman%20and%20Blania%2C%20a%20young%20German%20theoretical%20physicist%20who%20was%20previously%20a%20graduate%20student%20in%20Southern%20California%2C%20co-founded%20the%20companies%2C%20after%20Altman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-openai-chatgpt-worldcoin-helion-future-tech-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epitched%20him%20on%20the%20idea%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20cappuccinos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20overarching%20goal%2C%20Blania%20said%20on%20the%202022%20podcast%2C%20was%20scaling%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverything%20is%20optimized%20around%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BHow%20do%20we%20get%20to%20this%20billion-user%20number%20as%20quickly%20as%20we%20can%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e2d6a22d-62de-4fe4-8df9-5e5fc3bbf36f%5C%22%3EA%20billion%20eyeballs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20quest%20to%20reach%20that%20goal%2C%20the%20company%20has%20relied%20on%20outside%20funding%2C%20taking%20in%20nearly%20a%20quarter%20of%20a%20billion%20dollars%20over%20four%20rounds%20of%20funding%2C%20according%20to%20Pitchbook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20expanded%20into%20the%20UK%20and%20the%20US%2C%20with%20eye-scanning%20stores%20popping%20up%20from%20London%20to%20Los%20Angeles.%20It%20announced%20a%20pilot%20program%20with%20Match%20Group%20to%20verify%20Tinder%20users%20in%20Japan%20and%20partnerships%20with%20companies%20like%20Stripe%2C%20Visa%2C%20and%20the%20gaming%20company%20Razer.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.semafor.com%2Farticle%2F06%2F20%2F2025%2Freddit-considers-iris-scanning-orb-developed-by-a-sam-altman-startup%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReporting%20in%20Semafor%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June%20also%20said%20that%20Reddit%20was%20in%20talks%20with%20Tools%20for%20Humanity%20to%20use%20its%20verification%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Orb%20rollouts%20are%20expensive.%20Blania%20said%20last%20April%20that%20the%20company%20had%20already%20spent%20millions%20of%20dollars%20to%20develop%20and%20bring%20them%20to%20market.%20Two%20former%20employees%20said%20that%20each%20device%20had%20cost%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20to%20produce.%20Even%20so%2C%20five%20people%20said%20the%20Orbs%20often%20faced%20connectivity%20issues%20in%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20concern%20was%20revenue%2C%20former%20employees%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20the%20first%20question%20we%20got%20from%20regulators%2C%20like%2C%20'This%20sounds%20great%2C%20but%20how%20do%20you%20make%20money%3F'%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20former%20employee%20involved%20with%20Latin%20America%20expansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaynard%2C%20of%20Juniper%20Research%2C%20agreed.%20%26quot%3BUntil%20they%20have%20that%20scale%20and%20the%20platform%20sort%20of%20becomes%20self-sustaining%20then%20they're%20going%20to%20be%20burning%20through%20cash%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223797%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alex%20Blania%20speaks%20onstage%20during%20Sam%20Altman's%20World%20Celebration%20for%20the%20US%20Launch%20at%20Fort%20Mason%20Center%20on%20April%2030%2C%202025%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20California.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690e41f97f37aa653f55a50a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222580%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlex%20Blania%20speaks%20onstage%20during%20World's%20US%20launch%20event%20in%20San%20Francisco%20on%20April%2030%2C%202025.%3Cp%3EKimberly%20White%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20World%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20doesn't%20charge%20users%20to%20access%20its%20platforms%2C%20and%20Blania%20has%20said%20that%20the%20company%20won't%20become%20a%20data%20broker.%20Still%2C%20there%20are%20some%20potential%20revenue%20streams%3A%20Last%20spring%2C%20the%20company%20introduced%20World%20ID%20fees%2C%20a%20charge%20for%20when%20apps%20use%20the%20company's%20services.%20And%20it%20introduced%20a%20community%20operator%20program%20that%20allows%20people%20to%20rent%20or%20purchase%20their%20own%20Orbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20former%20employee%20said%20that%20the%20company%20also%20collected%20sequencer%20fees%20%E2%80%94%20the%20charge%20to%20process%20transactions%20%E2%80%94%20for%20World's%20blockchain%2C%20called%20World%20Chain.%20This%20person%2C%20who%20had%20knowledge%20of%20the%20financial%20impacts%20of%20Worldcoin%2C%20said%20he%20did%20not%20believe%20those%20fees%20alone%20would%20generate%20profit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20employee%20said%20the%20company's%20financial%20future%20depended%20on%20continued%20investor%20interest.%20%26quot%3BAs%20long%20as%20VC%20money%20is%20flowing%20in%2C%20and%20there's%20VCs%20that%20see%20value%20in%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20this%20person%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20will%20stay%20afloat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20people%20said%20that%20while%20the%20company's%20services%20could%20be%20useful%20in%20the%20future%2C%20they%20questioned%20what%20problem%20the%20company%20was%20trying%20to%20solve%20today.%20They've%20%26quot%3Bstill%20yet%20to%20provide%20an%20actual%20benefit%20for%20people%20besides%20the%20fact%20they're%20giving%20the%20cryptocurrency%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20former%20Germany-based%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMartha%20Bennett%2C%20vice%20president%20and%20principal%20analyst%20at%20the%20global%20research%20and%20advisory%20firm%20Forrester%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forrester.com%2Fblogs%2Fthe-web-needs-a-way-of-proving-that-youre-a-real-person-worldcoin-is-not-the-solution%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20previously%20been%20critical%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20project%2C%20was%20more%20blunt%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20actually%20have%20trouble%20seeing%20it%20as%20a%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20isn't%20an%20incentive%20around%20buying%20or%20leasing%20an%20Orb%20other%20than%20making%20money%20off%20of%20it%20by%20scanning%20loads%20of%20eyeballs%2C%20and%20for%20the%20users%2C%20it's%20to%20get%20some%20more%20coins.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20crypto%20experts%20who%20spoke%20to%20Business%20Insider%20raised%20questions%20over%20the%20long-term%20viability%20of%20Worldcoin%2C%20which%20has%20less%20than%200.1%25%20of%20Bitcoin's%20roughly%20%242%20trillion%20market%20cap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20just%20hard%20to%20judge%20something%20that's%20a%20crypto%20with%20a%20%242%20billion%20market%20cap%20as%20anything%20other%20than%20experimental%20or%20a%20fad%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nikhil%20Bhatia%2C%20a%20finance%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California%20who%20studies%20cryptocurrency.%20%26quot%3BWorldcoin%20is%20not%20a%20contender%20in%20any%20way%20for%20currency%20or%20an%20asset%20relative%20to%20the%20dollar%20or%20Bitcoin.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2228776ad7-9e4e-4ec8-8181-d2ff0e898401%5C%22%3EA%20world%20of%20trouble%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETools%20for%20Humanity's%20model%20involved%20working%20with%20independent%20contractors%20across%20the%20world%20who%20oversaw%20Orb%20scanning.%20These%20contractors%20were%20paid%20on%20a%20commission%20basis%20for%20each%20user%20they%20signed%20up%2C%20often%20in%20Worldcoin%2C%20according%20to%20former%20employees%20and%20people%20involved%20with%20iris%20scanning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuis%20Ruben%20De%20Valad%C3%A9z%20worked%20as%20head%20of%20operations%20for%20a%20company%20in%20Mexico%20that%20contracted%20with%20Tools%20for%20Humanity%2C%20and%20he%20said%20he%20helped%20open%20seven%20stores%20across%20Mexico%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETools%20for%20Humanity%20covered%20the%20rent%20for%20up%20to%20a%20year%20and%20reimbursed%20the%20company%20monthly%20with%20Worldcoin%3B%20De%20Valad%C3%A9z%20said%20his%20employer%20was%20on%20the%20hook%20financially%20for%20all%20other%20costs.%20He%20relied%20on%20family%20and%20friends%20to%20raise%20around%20100%2C000%20pesos%2C%20about%20%245%2C400%2C%20for%20those%20expansion%20efforts.%20(He%20said%20that%20some%20of%20these%20funds%20were%20ultimately%20returned%20if%20not%20used.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDe%20Valad%C3%A9z%20said%20that%20while%20he%20had%20a%20largely%20positive%20experience%20with%20the%20company%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20would%20have%20been%20nice%20to%20have%20some%20more%20support%20on%20the%20financial%20side%20of%20things%20for%20the%20operators%20since%20we're%20the%20ones%20operating%20and%20in%20the%20field.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227284%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20looking%20at%20an%20Orb%2C%20while%20a%20salesperson%20points%20at%20it%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6911eae146c4547ecb0575db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224856%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20man%20has%20his%20iris%20scanned%20with%20an%20Orb%20in%20Buenos%20Aires%2C%20Argentina%2C%20in%20March%202024.%3Cp%3EJUAN%20MABROMATA%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20former%20employees%20described%20the%20company's%20early%20strategy%20in%20some%20countries%20as%20asking%20for%20forgiveness%2C%20not%20permission%20%E2%80%94%20reminiscent%20of%20the%20fast-growing%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-company-scandals-and-controversies-2017-11%23march-2017-the-new-york-times-reveals-uber-has-been-secretly-deceiving-authorities-for-years-with-a-tool-called-greyball-26%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escandal-plagued%20early%20days%20of%20Uber%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20dozens%20of%20current%20and%20former%20Tools%20for%20Humanity%20employees%20previously%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20on%2C%20the%20company%20appeared%20to%20launch%20in%20places%20where%20people%20would%20be%20attracted%20by%20the%20promise%20of%20free%20crypto.%20During%20a%20recent%20city%20council%20session%20in%20Brazil%2C%20Bruno%20Bioni%2C%20founding%20director%20of%20the%20digital%20rights%20nonprofit%20Data%20Privacy%20Brazil%2C%20said%20that%20many%20people%20scanning%20their%20irises%20were%20socioeconomically%20vulnerable%20and%20incentivized%20by%20the%20financial%20compensation%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sentiment%20echoed%20by%20former%20workers%20who%20spoke%20to%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20sources%20said%20it%20was%20common%20for%20users%20to%20exchange%20their%20tokens%20for%20hard%20currency%20following%20the%20scans.%20In%20Latin%20America%2C%20currency%20exchanges%20where%20cash%20was%20given%20for%20the%20crypto%20often%20popped%20up%20around%20the%20Orb%20stations%2C%20according%20to%20four%20people%20and%20photos%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20Similar%20scenarios%20unfolded%20in%20Kenya%2C%20said%20an%20Orb%20operator%20who%20worked%20there.%20(In%20May%2C%20Kenya's%20High%20Court%20declared%20World's%20operations%20unlawful%20and%20ordered%20it%20to%20permanently%20delete%20biometric%20data.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20changed%20its%20policies%20in%20response%20to%20these%20crypto%20exchanges%2C%20two%20people%20said%2C%20so%20that%20users%20wouldn't%20receive%20crypto%20until%20at%20least%20a%20day%20after%20the%20iris%20scans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Tools%20for%20Humanity%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20company%20engages%20in%20ongoing%20discussions%20with%20regulators%2C%20and%20works%20closely%20with%20stakeholders%2C%20in%20the%20countries%20where%20it%20operates.%20The%20former%20employee%20involved%20with%20Latin%20American%20expansion%20also%20said%20that%20their%20team%20prioritized%20talking%20to%20regulators%20to%20explain%20the%20project%20and%20privacy%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPrior%20to%20launching%20in%20a%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWorld%20conducts%20extensive%20research%20and%20analysis%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20project's%20operations%20and%20services%20are%20compliant%20with%20applicable%20rules%20and%20regulations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20other%20problems.%20In%20Argentina%2C%20unaffiliated%20third-party%20organizers%20bused%20people%20to%20iris%20scanning%20locations%20to%20receive%20crypto%20payments%2C%20according%20to%20former%20employees%20and%20local%20news%20coverage.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20these%20third%20parties%20handed%20out%20phones%20to%20people%20prior%20to%20the%20scans%20and%20then%20took%20them%20back%20after%20verification%2C%20according%20to%20two%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELocal%20media%20in%20the%20Argentine%20province%20of%20Chaco%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.diariotag.com%2F167268-llego-a-chaco-un-micro-con-55-personas-que-viajaron-a-escanearse-el-iris-de-sus-ojos-voluntariament%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%20that%20authorities%20stopped%20a%20bus%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20May%202024%20carrying%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.diariochaco.com%2F655302-escaneo-de-iris-por-dinero-interceptan-un-micro-repleto-de-pasajeros-que-regreso-de-buenos-aires%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E55%20people%20returning%20from%20Bue