f%20the%20everyday%20millionaire%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20number%20of%20people%20globally%20with%20%241%20to%20%245%20million%20in%20investable%20assets%20has%20quadrupled%20to%2052%20million%20in%20the%20last%2025%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20megarich%20have%20multiplied%2C%20so%20too%20have%20their%20mansions%2C%20planes%2C%20and%20yachts%20that%20need%20to%20be%20staffed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cassidy%20O'Hagan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F691231900a30027667eb04aa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECassidy%20O'Hagan%3Cp%3ECassidy%20O'Hagan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20so%20many%20wealthy%20people%2C%20and%20they're%20not%20just%20buying%20one%20estate%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniel%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20never%20been%20a%20better%20opportunity%20in%20history%20to%20get%20into%20private%20service%2C%20because%20each%20one%20of%20these%20billionaires%20employs%20small%20armies%20of%20people%20to%20cater%20to%20their%20every%20whim.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20post-pandemic%20hiring%20spree%20has%20also%20created%20bidding%20wars%20within%20the%20industry%2C%20driving%20up%20salaries%20and%20perks.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20very%20severe%20shortage%20across%20the%20board%20of%20elite%20staff%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniel%20says.%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20you%20need%20a%20place%20to%20stay%3F%20Here's%20the%20guest%20house.%20Oh%2C%20you%20need%20a%20company%20car%3F%20Here%20you%20go.%20A%20401k%2C%20guaranteed%20hours%20%E2%80%94%20I%20mean%2C%20they're%20throwing%20in%20the%20kitchen%20sink.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20look%20at%20open%20roles%20on%20the%20staffing%20agency%20Tiger%20Recruitment's%20website%20was%20illustrative.%20There%20was%20a%20listing%20for%20a%20housekeeper%20that%20pays%20up%20to%20%24120%2C000%2C%20and%20a%20nanny%20that%20pays%20up%20to%20%24150%2C000.%20There%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bhead%20of%20personal%20assistants%26quot%3B%20with%20a%20salary%20range%20of%20%24250%2C000%20to%20%24280%2C000%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bdirector%20of%20residences%26quot%3B%20that%20jets%20between%20properties%20in%20New%20York%2C%20East%20Hampton%2C%20Aspen%2C%20and%20Bel%20Air%20for%20%24200%2C000%20to%20%24250%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20O'Hagan%20started%20looking%20to%20work%20for%20a%20high-net-worth%20family%20in%202019%2C%20she%20was%2022%20and%20looking%20to%20earn%20extra%20money%20while%20preparing%20for%20the%20MCAT.%20Soon%20after%20landing%20her%20first%20job%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20realized%20very%20quickly%20after%20moving%20in%20that%20I%20had%20stepped%20into%20this%20completely%20different%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDetails%20in%20the%20interview%20were%20scant%2C%20but%20when%20she%20arrived%20at%20the%20family's%20California%20mansion%20she%20learned%20that%20%26quot%3Bcovered%20meals%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20job%20description%20turned%20out%20to%20mean%20an%20in-house%20chef%20who%20not%20only%20cooked%20on-site%20for%20the%20family%2C%20but%20for%20an%20entire%20domestic%20staff.%20O'Hagan%20was%20one%20of%20four%20nannies%20on%20a%20%26quot%3Bchildcare%20team%26quot%3B%20working%20for%20a%20couple%20in%20their%20mid-30s%20from%20a%20big-name%20business%20family.%20There%20were%20personal%20assistants%2C%20a%20roster%20of%20housekeepers%2C%20a%20chief%20of%20staff%20of%20the%20home%2C%20and%20even%20a%20dedicated%20home%20organizer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESatisfying%20as%20the%20work%20was%2C%20she%20still%20planned%20to%20build%20a%20career%20in%20healthcare.%20%26quot%3BI%20definitely%20had%20internalized%20this%20message%20that%20no%20matter%20how%20professional%20or%20demanding%20or%20meaningful%20my%20job%20was%2C%20being%20a%20nanny%20was%20just%20not%20enough.%20So%20I%20kind%20of%20forced%20myself%20into%20corporate%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20she%20moved%20to%20New%20York%20City%20for%20a%20job%20in%20medical%20sales%20at%20a%20large%20company.%20She%20spent%20long%20hours%20in%20surgeries%20and%20at%20hospitals%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20male-dominated%26quot%3B%20environment%2C%20O'Hagan%20says.%20Her%20entry-level%20%2465%2C000%20salary%20also%20didn't%20go%20very%20far%20in%20the%20city.%20Soon%2C%20she%20felt%20burnt%20out%20and%20invisible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20realized%20that%20I%20had%20walked%20away%20from%20work%20that%20actually%20aligned%20with%20who%20I%20was%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bsomeone%20who's%20very%20nurturing%20and%20personable%20and%20intuitive%20and%20service%20based.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20less%20than%20a%20year%2C%20she%20quit%20and%20got%20back%20into%20nannying%20%E2%80%94%20this%20time%20with%20the%20intention%20to%20build%20a%20career%20and%20work%20for%20families%20who%20were%20next-level%20wealthy.%20%26quot%3BBeing%20in%20New%20York%2C%20I%20knew%20there%20are%20billionaires%20here%2C%20there%20are%20ultra%20high%20net%20worth%20families%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20really%20wanting%20to%20go%20to%20the%20top.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20started%20working%20with%20private%20staffing%20agencies%2C%20and%20landed%20a%20rotational%20nanny%20position%20with%20what%20she%20describes%20as%20a%20well-known%20New%20York%20family.%20Her%20income%20went%20up%20by%20%2440K%20instantly.%20She%20also%20had%20chef-made%20meals%20again%2C%20an%20entire%20wardrobe%20provided%20to%20her%20by%20the%20family%2C%20and%20got%20to%20ditch%20the%20subway%20thanks%20to%20covered%20Uber%20rides%20to%20and%20from%20work.%20It%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20night%20and%20day%26quot%3B%20switch%20from%20the%20corporate%20grind%20%E2%80%94%20and%20she%20hasn't%20looked%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Gen%20Z%20has%20grown%20more%20disillusioned%20with%20corporate%20life%2C%20O'Hagan%20is%20far%20from%20alone%20in%20her%20pivot.%20A%202025%20Deloitte%20survey%20found%20that%20only%206%25%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20say%20their%20primary%20career%20goal%20is%20to%20reach%20a%20leadership%20position%20at%20work.%20Some%20are%20even%20avoiding%20taking%20on%20managerial%20roles%20at%20all%20(it's%20called%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-consciously-unbossing-avoid-management-roles-preserve-mental-health-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econscious%20unbossing%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B)%20to%20prioritize%20work-life%20balance.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20they%20also%20expect%20to%20earn%20more%2C%20a%20lot%20more%2C%20than%20older%20generations.%20Per%20a%20recent%20Empower%20survey%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20define%20financial%20success%20as%20a%20salary%20of%20nearly%20%24600%2C000%2C%20about%20six%20times%20higher%20than%20what%20Boomers%20said.%20And%20yet%2C%20post-grads%20have%20been%20particularly%20vocal%20about%20their%20inability%20to%20get%20jobs%20as%20hiring%20across%20US%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjuly-jobs-report-unemployment-rate-employment-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereached%20a%20lull%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20months%20and%20AI%20continues%20to%20creep%20into%20corporate%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivate%20staffing%20has%20always%20been%20a%20career%20that%20people%20sort%20of%20fall%20into%2C%20says%20Daniel.%20What's%20different%20today%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20only%20are%20the%20newer%20players%20these%20days%20in%20the%20industry%20younger%2C%20they're%20college%20educated%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20get%20emails%20from%20people%20who%20have%20PhDs%2C%20people%20who%20were%20lawyers%2C%20people%20who%20were%20business%20owners%2C%20people%20who%20were%20in%20real%20estate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20newcomers%20is%20Julia%20Dudley.%20The%2026-year-old%20got%20her%20undergrad%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20master's%20degree%20in%20communications%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20went%20to%20culinary%20school.%20But%20she%20eventually%20ditched%20both%20agency%20and%20restaurant%20work%20in%20favor%20of%20building%20a%20meal%20prep%20business%20and%20working%20as%20a%20private%20chef.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20okay%2C%20I%20can%20make%20my%20own%20hours%2C%20I%20can%20make%20more%20money%2C%20I'm%20my%20own%20boss%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20way%20more%20interesting%20to%20me%20than%20being%20on%20the%20line%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20restaurant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Julia%20Dudley%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F691230c90a30027667eb0493%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJulia%20Dudley%20on%20the%20job%20cooking%20for%20a%20client%20in%20the%20Hamptons%20earlier%20this%20year.%3Cp%3EJulia%20Dudley%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20has%20spent%20the%20last%20few%20summers%20cooking%20for%20families%20in%20the%20Hamptons%2C%20where%20she%20says%20cooking%20two%20or%20three%20meals%20a%20day%20for%20a%20few%20months%20can%20pay%20a%20six-figure%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20chefs%20will%20leave%20the%20five%20star%20restaurant%20and%20go%20into%20private%20service%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Daniel.%20%26quot%3BWe%20know%20how%20long%20and%20grueling%20it%20can%20be%2C%20but%20you%20can%20triple%20your%20salary%20by%20leaving%20the%20restaurant%20and%20going%20into%20private%20service%20and%20working%20for%20a%20billionaire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20for%20a%20billionaire%20can%20also%20be%20nerve-racking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20you're%20paid%20well%20is%20because%20you're%20expected%20to%20be%20on%20call%20outside%20the%20usual%209-to-5%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20roles%2C%20and%20sometimes%20you'll%20be%20expected%20to%20work%20long%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Ruth%20Edwards%2C%20a%20private%20staffing%20recruiter%20at%20Tiger%20who%20specializes%20in%20family%20offices%20and%20private%20residences%20of%20ultra-high-net-worth%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20this%20industry%20with%20the%20celebrities%20and%20billionaires%2C%20you%20have%20to%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20energy%20because%20it's%20always%20breakneck%20speeds%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Daniel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20must%20be%20willing%20to%20do%20whatever%20is%20necessary%20to%20help%20the%20%26quot%3Bprinciple%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20industry%20term%20for%20the%20client.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20housekeeper%20went%20home%20and%20the%20dog%20did%20some%20doo-doo%20in%20the%20living%20room%20and%20you're%20there%20with%20the%20VIP%2C%20somebody%20has%20to%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThen%20what%20happens%20is%2C%20you%20do%20something%20like%20that%2C%20and%2030%20minutes%20later%20or%20an%20hour%20later%2C%20maybe%20you're%20sitting%20in%20a%20movie%20studio%20with%20your%20boss%20helping%20him%20close%20a%20%2450%20million%20movie.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20stress%20can%20be%20more%20than%20even%20on%20Wall%20Street%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniel%20says%2C%20recalling%20a%20time%20he%20took%20himself%20to%20the%20hospital%20while%20having%20a%20panic%20attack%20after%20a%20particularly%20stressful%20day%20as%20an%20assistant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20O'Hagan%2C%20one%20challenge%20of%20working%20in%20the%20homes%20of%20the%20elite%20is%20that%20professional%20and%20personal%20life%20often%20blur%20together.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20just%20working%20for%20a%20family%2C%20you're%20living%20alongside%20them%2C%20immersed%20in%20their%20rhythms%2C%20dynamics%2C%20and%20private%20moments%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20She%20works%20across%20multiple%20international%20residences%20as%20one%20of%20eight%20nannies%2C%20but%20it%20can%20still%20be%20lonely.%20She's%20spent%20many%20holidays%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%20%E2%80%94%20Christmases%2C%20Thanksgivings%2C%20her%20birthday%2C%20family%20celebrations%20%E2%80%94%20with%20whatever%20family%20she's%20working%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20not%20simple%20to%20break%20in%20and%20land%20roles%20in%20top%20households.%20Discretion%20and%20privacy%20are%20tantamount%20%E2%80%94%20most%20ultra-high-net-worth%20families%20have%20their%20staff%20sign%20extensive%20NDAs%2C%20and%20require%20their%20staff%20to%20have%20very%20clean%20presences%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20also%20means%20staffing%20agencies%20are%20often%20doing%20the%20headhunting%20on%20behalf%20of%20their%20wealthy%20clients.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20very%20cutthroat%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Hagan%20says%2C%20and%20the%20often%20the%20only%20way%20to%20even%20meet%20a%20family%20is%20to%20get%20represented%20by%20an%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you%20get%20past%20that%2C%20private%20service%20quickly%20rewards%20excellence%2C%20says%20Daniel.%20He%20represented%20a%20Hollywood%20actor's%20personal%20driver%20who%20over%2015%20years%20became%20a%20personal%20assistant%20to%20the%20principle%2C%20then%20a%20executive%20assistant%2C%20and%20eventually%20was%20co-producing%20films%20with%20him%20and%20making%20%26quot%3Bfabulous%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EO'Hagan%20adds%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20dreamed%20of%20working%20for%20the%20world's%20most%20elite%20families%20at%20one%20point%2C%20and%20in%20just%20five%20years%20I%20reached%20that%20goal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20eventually%20wants%20to%20move%20on%20from%20nannying.%20She's%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20starting%20her%20own%20agency%20and%20coaching%20business%20to%20help%20other%20young%20people%20break%20in%2C%20which%20she%20hopes%20will%20her%20the%20flexibility%20to%20start%20start%20her%20own%20family%20one%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeers%20of%20mine%20who%20are%20in%20corporate%20in%20New%20York%20City%20and%20young%20girls%20that%20I'm%20connected%20with%20have%20reached%20out%20to%20me%20so%20many%20times%20as