omu-okruzi-rf-narakhuvaly-ponad-600-zahyblykh-cherez-khaos-antysanitariiu-i-narkotyky%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20in%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20deceased%20reported%20to%20Russia's%20Central%20Military%20District%2C%20one%20of%20five%20jurisdictions%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20district%20covers%20central%20Russia%2C%20encompassing%20regions%20that%20host%20nearly%2040%25%20of%20the%20country's%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHUR%20wrote%20that%20%26quot%3Blow%20quality%20of%20food%26quot%3B%20among%20Russia's%20military%20units%20led%20to%2032%20of%20the%20district's%20troops%20dying%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-resistance-fighters-mariupol-poisoned-russia-soldiers-food-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efood%20poisoning%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20added%20that%20at%20least%20112%20Russian%20troops%20have%20died%20from%20drug%20abuse%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20year%2C%20while%20another%20143%20died%20from%20drug%20poisoning%20in%20the%20whole%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20157%20Russian%20soldiers%20from%20the%20district%20died%20from%20suicide%20in%20the%20same%20timeframe%2C%20HUR%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ukrainian%20agency%20did%20not%20say%20how%20it%20acquired%20this%20information%2C%20and%20Business%20Insider%20could%20not%20independently%20verify%20HUR's%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20report%20comes%20after%20Ukrainian%20units%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-latest-offensive-squandered-golden-opportunity-in-kharkiv-experts-ukraine-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enorthern%20Kharkiv%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20September%202024%20that%20they%20had%20found%20cases%20of%20mass%20food%20poisoning%20among%20the%20ranks%20of%20Russia's%2011th%20Tank%20Regiment%20of%20the%2018th%20Motorized%20Rifle%20Division.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2018th%20Motorized%20Rifle%20Division%2C%20however%2C%20belongs%20to%20the%20Leningrad%20Military%20District.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20increase%20in%20the%20level%20of%20suicides%2C%20crime%2C%20and%20drug%20abuse%20among%20the%20Russian%20military%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20the%20deep%20demoralization%20of%20the%20occupation%20contingent%2C%26quot%3B%20HUR%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20defense%20ministry%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrug%20abuse%20among%20Russian%20troops%20has%20been%20regularly%20reported%20on%20the%20front%20lines.%20In%20late%202023%2C%20the%20independent%20Russian%20outlet%20Vertska%20reported%20that%20up%20to%2015%25%20of%20Russian%20soldiers%20in%20combat%20zones%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-soldiers-get-drugs-sent-to-trenches-are-bored-report-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etaking%20substances%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20mephedrone%2C%20amphetamines%2C%20and%20alpha-PVP%2C%20which%20is%20also%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bsalt.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UK%20defense%20ministry%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FDefenceHQ%2Fstatus%2F1724042993638715596%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20November%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20that%20year%20that%20it%20had%20similarly%20observed%20repeated%20reports%20of%20%26quot%3Bdisciplinary%20incidents%2C%20crimes%2C%20and%20deaths%20related%20to%20alcohol%20abuse%26quot%3B%20among%20Russian%20troops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20number%20of%20non-combat%20deaths%20reported%20by%20HUR%20on%20Monday%20is%20just%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20the%20total%20Russian%20force%20deployed%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20estimates%20from%20Kyiv%20indicate%20that%20Russia%20now%20stations%20a%20total%20of%20about%20700%2C000%20troops%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20while%20international%20analysts%20have%20said%20the%20number%20may%20be%20around%20600%2C000%20troop