against%20peers%20or%20any%20other%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20pay%20ratio%20reported%20by%20other%20companies%20may%20not%20be%20comparable%20because%20companies%20have%20different%20employee%20populations%20and%20compensation%20practices%20and%20may%20utilize%20different%20methodologies%2C%20exclusions%2C%20estimates%2C%20and%20assumptions%20in%20calculating%20their%20own%20ratios%2C%26quot%3B%20Starbucks%20said%20in%20its%20most%20recent%20filing%2C%20for%20example.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20CEO%2C%20Brian%20Niccol%2C%20made%20%2497.8%20million%20last%20year%20%E2%80%94%206%2C666%20times%20the%20median%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20companies%2C%20like%20Costco%20and%20Amazon%2C%20have%20chosen%20to%20disclose%20more%20information%20than%20the%20rules%20require%20by%20identifying%20a%20supplemental%20median%20employee%20from%20their%20US-based%2C%20full-time%2C%20full-year%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20adjustment%20results%20in%20a%20higher-paid%20median%20worker%20and%20narrows%20Costco's%20CEO%20pay%20ratio%20from%20262%3A1%20to%20192%3A1%2C%20and%20Amazon's%20from%2043%3A1%20to%2033%3A1.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20consultant%20ever%20recommended%20a%20serious%20cut%20in%20CEO%20compensation%20or%20board%20payments%3F%26quot%3B%20Buffett%20asked%20in%20his%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBerkshire%20Hathaway's%20proxy%20statement%20from%20earlier%20this%20year%20includes%20its%20own%20critiques%20of%20the%20SEC%20rules%2C%20noting%20that%20Buffett's%20salary%20has%20been%20%24100%2C000%20for%20more%20than%2040%20years%2C%20plus%20%24305%2C111%20in%20home%20and%20personal%20security%20expenses.%20With%20the%20median%20employee%20earning%20%2482%2C106%2C%20Buffett's%20pay%20ratio%20was%204.94%3A1.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuffett-said-ceo-to-employee-pay-comparison-rule-backfired-letter-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22