ment%2C%20honesty%2C%20and%20choosing%20the%20right%20leaders.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BChoose%20your%20heroes%20very%20carefully%20and%20then%20emulate%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20be%20a%20high-mileage%20CEO%20like%20Warren%20Buffett%2C%20it%20pays%20to%20be%20humble.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20advice%20from%20the%20Oracle%20of%20Omaha%2C%20in%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-warren-buffett-thanksgiving-shareholder-letter-full-text-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinal%20Thanksgiving%20letter%20to%20shareholders%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20CEO%20of%20Berkshire%20Hathaway%2C%20released%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuffett%20detailed%20a%20range%20of%20thoughts%20on%20the%20virtues%20of%20stewardship%2C%20honesty%2C%20and%20what%20he%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bgood%20intentions%26quot%3B%20gone%20awry%20in%20attempts%20to%20rein%20in%20CEO%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20broad%20takeaway%20was%20his%20call%20to%20continue%20learning%20and%20growing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChoose%20your%20heroes%20very%20carefully%20and%20then%20emulate%20them.%20You%20will%20never%20be%20perfect%2C%20but%20you%20can%20always%20be%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20Buffett%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20five%20other%20lessons%20Buffett%20shared%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22456e7141-e905-4f77-a56d-e466e7dd5705%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EStay%20humble%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2095-year-old%20has%20famously%20run%20the%20conglomerate%20with%20an%20unfussy%2C%20meat-and-potatoes%20sensibility%20for%20more%20than%20five%20decades.%20Buffett%20wrote%20about%20the%20role%20luck%20played%20in%20his%20life%20and%20work%2C%20and%20how%20that%20experience%20continually%20honed%20his%20sense%20of%20humility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BKeep%20in%20mind%20that%20the%20cleaning%20lady%20is%20as%20much%20a%20human%20being%20as%20the%20Chairman%2C%26quot%3B%20Buffett%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20grounded%20some%20of%20his%20humble%20inclinations%20in%20the%20luck%20he%20had%2C%20being%20a%20man%20%E2%80%94%20compared%20with%20his%20sisters%2C%20whom%20he%20described%20as%20having%20%26quot%3Bequal%20intelligence%20and%20better%20personalities%2C%26quot%3B%20though%20they%20faced%20a%20much%20different%20outlook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20born%20in%201930%20healthy%2C%20reasonably%20intelligent%2C%20white%2C%20male%20and%20in%20America.%20Wow!%20Thank%20you%2C%20Lady%20Luck%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22077accb8-d88e-4799-a4e5-bd429aefd90c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELearn%20from%20your%20errors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBuffett%20said%20that%20while%20he's%20made%20many%20mistakes%2C%20he's%20tried%20to%20use%20them%20as%20opportunities.%20%26quot%3BLearn%20at%20least%20a%20little%20from%20them%20and%20move%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Buffett%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20misstep%2C%20he%20said%2C%20was%20not%20intervening%20more%20forcefully%20when%20he%20saw%20indications%20that%20a%20%26quot%3Bwonderful%20and%20loyal%20CEO%26quot%3B%20of%20a%20parent%20or%20subsidiary%20company%20would%20%26quot%3Bsuccumb%20to%20dementia%2C%20Alzheimer's%20or%20another%20debilitating%20and%20long-term%20disease.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCharlie%20and%20I%20encountered%20this%20problem%20several%20times%20and%20failed%20to%20act.%20This%20failure%20can%20be%20a%20huge%20mistake%2C%26quot%3B%20Buffett%20wrote%2C%20referring%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarren-buffett-charlie-munger-berkshire-hathaway-partnership-friendship-2019-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECharlie%20Munger%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20his%20longtime%20friend%20and%20colleague%2C%20who%20died%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuffett%20said%20that%20while%20it's%20often%20not%20easy%2C%20boards%20need%20to%20keep%20watch%20for%20signs%20of%20such%20conditions%20in%20chiefs%2C%20and%20that%20CEOs%20themselves%20